<refsect1 id="GnomeCanvasRichText.description" role="desc">
<title role="desc.title">Description</title>

<para>
A canvas item that displays a GtkTextBuffer which is a flexible text display
and editing widget. Consult GtkTextBuffer info in the GTK+ Reference
documentation for more details.
</para>
</refsect1>

<refsect1 id="GnomeCanvasRichText.details" role="details">
<title role="details.title">Details</title>
<refsect2 id="GnomeCanvasRichText-struct" role="struct">
<title>GnomeCanvasRichText</title>
<indexterm zone="GnomeCanvasRichText-struct"><primary>GnomeCanvasRichText</primary></indexterm>
<programlisting>typedef struct _GnomeCanvasRichText GnomeCanvasRichText;</programlisting>
<para>
This structure should not be accessed directly. Use the object's properties
and functions for querying or changing its parameters.
</para></refsect2>
<refsect2 id="gnome-canvas-rich-text-cut-clipboard" role="function">
<title>gnome_canvas_rich_text_cut_clipboard ()</title>
<indexterm zone="gnome-canvas-rich-text-cut-clipboard"><primary>gnome_canvas_rich_text_cut_clipboard</primary></indexterm>
<programlisting><link linkend="void">void</link>                gnome_canvas_rich_text_cut_clipboard
                                                        (<link linkend="GnomeCanvasRichText">GnomeCanvasRichText</link> *text);</programlisting>
<para>
Copies the currently selected <parameter>text</parameter> to clipboard, then deletes said text
if it's editable.</para>
<para>
</para><variablelist role="params">
<varlistentry><term><parameter>text</parameter>&#160;:</term>
<listitem><simpara> a <link linkend="GnomeCanvasRichText."><type>GnomeCanvasRichText.</type></link>
</simpara></listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist></refsect2>
